<paragraph id="8B823C6AFFC9F5180CE9DA81FE56F8A9" blockId="36.[168,488,1776,1800]" box="[168,488,1776,1800]" pageId="36" pageNumber="543">
<heading id="D0CA8B06FFC9F5180CE9DA81FE56F8A9" box="[168,488,1776,1800]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="36" pageNumber="543" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="4C3D47E9FFC9F5180CE9DA81FE56F8A9" authority="Hitchc." box="[168,488,1776,1800]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Sporobolus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="36" pageNumber="543" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cubensis">
<emphasis id="B949E078FFC9F5180CE9DA81FE56F8A9" bold="true" box="[168,488,1776,1800]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="543" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B949E078FFC9F5180CE9DA81FE30F8A9" bold="true" box="[168,398,1776,1800]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="543">Sporobolus cubensis</emphasis>
Hitchc.
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823C6AFFC9F5180CE9DB69FEE6F818" blockId="36.[168,778,1816,1977]" pageId="36" pageNumber="543">
<emphasis id="B949E078FFC9F5180CE9DB69FEF4F891" bold="true" box="[168,330,1816,1840]" pageId="36" pageNumber="543">Identification.</emphasis>
Perennial tussock grass, 
<quantity id="4CC5918FFFC9F5180ED3DB69FCB4F88E" box="[658,778,1816,1840]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="36" pageNumber="543" unit="cm" value="60.0" valueMax="70.0" valueMin="50.0">50–70 cm</quantity>
height. Leaf-blades lanceolate with trichomes on the margin, 
<quantity id="4CC5918FFFC9F5180D44DB2CFECEF8D5" box="[261,368,1885,1909]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="36" pageNumber="543" unit="cm" value="16.5" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="10.0">10–23 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CC5918FFFC9F5180DF7DB2CFD8EF8D5" box="[438,560,1885,1909]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="36" pageNumber="543" unit="cm" value="0.35" valueMax="0.4" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.4 cm</quantity>
wide, ligulate. Distinguished by its open panicle, 
<quantity id="4CC5918FFFC9F5180DBDDB0EFDE7F837" box="[508,601,1919,1943]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="36" pageNumber="543" unit="cm" value="11.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="8.0">8–15 cm</quantity>
long with verticillate branches.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3276FE1FFC9F5180CE9DBB8FD19F7A2" pageId="36" pageNumber="543" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B823C6AFFC9F5180CE9DBB8FD19F7A2" blockId="36.[168,777,1993,2051]" pageId="36" pageNumber="543">
<emphasis id="B949E078FFC9F5180CE9DBB8FEA9F840" bold="true" box="[168,279,1993,2017]" pageId="36" pageNumber="543">Remarks.</emphasis>
Relatively common species on the native grassland, occurring mainly over shallow soils.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
